    <div class="article-teaser">
        Transport for London (TfL) will shortly be launching its 2008 graduate recruitment scheme.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<p>
<p>The organisation has been voted by graduates across the UK as one of the Top 100 employers in the Times' Graduate Employer of Choice awards.</p>
<p>With graduate schemes in 14 different, company-wide disciplines, TfL is this year supporting more than 100 new graduate trainees who are starting careers in their chosen professions.</p>
<p>The scheme offers a wide range of options for successful applicants including positions in management, engineering, IT, finance or transport planning.</p>
<p>Find out more at TfL's Graduate Open Day </p>
<p>If you want to find out more about the TfL's graduate opportunities in 2008, visit the team at Glaziers Hall, 9 Montague Close, London Bridge, SE1 on October 5 between 11am and 3pm. </p>
<p>For details, visit tfl.gov.uk/graduates</p>

     

        
        
        
